# Chapter 3 – Ubuntu Server Installation

## Objective

The objective of this chapter was to install and configure Ubuntu Server as the operating system that will host Splunk Enterprise for the SOC Detection and Monitoring Lab. This server will act as the centralized platform for log collection, analysis, and security monitoring throughout the project.

---

## Background

Ubuntu Server is a lightweight, stable, and widely used Linux server operating system. It is commonly deployed in enterprise environments to host services and applications such as SIEM platforms. In this lab, Ubuntu Server was selected to host Splunk Enterprise because of its stability, performance, and compatibility.

---

## Virtual Machine Specifications

| Specification | Value |
|--------------|-------|
| Operating System | Ubuntu Server 24.04 LTS |
| RAM | 1 GB |
| CPU | 1 Core |
| Disk Size | 10 GB |
| Installation Method | ISO Image |

---

## Installation Process

Ubuntu Server was installed using the official ISO image in Oracle VirtualBox. After completing the installation, the server was successfully booted and configured for internet connectivity. The operating system was then updated to ensure all installed packages were current before proceeding with additional software installation.

